column43: # zifishþ------þ基于spring boot的快速开发框架   þþspring-boot技术交流群：  604158262þþþþ## 环境要求和主要框架依赖版本þ- JDK 8+þ- Spring 4.x+þ- Spring Boot 1.5.16.RELEASE (boot模块要求）þ- Spring Cloud Edgware (cloud模块要求)þþ## maven   þ当前snapshot版本：**4.7.4-SNAPSHOT**   þþ若使用snapshot版本，请添加snapshotRepository仓储：   þ```xml   þ<repository>þ     <id>oss</id>þ     <url>https://oss.sonatype.org/content/repositories/snapshots/</url>þ    <snapshots>þ        <enabled>true</enabled>þ    </snapshots>þ</repository>   þ```þþ## 示例项目   þ基于zifish的web示例项目：þ[web-sample](https://github.com/wayshall/onetwo-web-sample)  þ基于zifish的后台管理示例项目：þ[web-manager](https://github.com/wayshall/onetwo-web-manager)   þþþ## [common模块](https://github.com/wayshall/onetwo/tree/master/core/modules/common)þ通用模块，一些工具类封装。þþ## [spring模块](https://github.com/wayshall/onetwo/tree/master/core/modules/spring)þ依赖到spring相关的封装þþþ## [内嵌tomcat模块](https://github.com/wayshall/onetwo/tree/master/core/modules/tomcat)þ简单的内嵌tomcat容器实现þþ## [poi模块](https://github.com/wayshall/onetwo/tree/master/core/modules/poi)þ基于poi，对操作excel的简单封装。þþ## [dbm模块](https://github.com/wayshall/dbm)þþ基于spring jdbc实现的简单orm   þþ单独使用dbm的示例项目：þ[boot-dbm-sample](https://github.com/wayshall/boot-dbm-sample)þþ## [security模块](https://github.com/wayshall/onetwo/tree/master/core/modules/security)þ基于spring security实现的动态 RBAC 权限管理  þþþ## [boot模块](https://github.com/wayshall/onetwo/tree/master/core/modules/boot)þboot模块：þ- 基于boot之上封装插件机制þ- freemarker增加插件路径分派支持þ- 封装第三方库使用þ  þþ## [zifish-plugins插件项目](https://github.com/wayshall/zifish-plugins)þ包含了基于本框架开发的插件。þ- web-admin插件：使用jquery-easyui编写的简单后台管理，包含了基本的权限管理和菜单功能。þ- swaggerext插件þþþ## 捐赠þ如果你觉得这个项目帮到了你，请用支付宝打赏一杯咖啡吧~~~   þþ![支付宝](doc/alipay2.jpg)

column17: Mybatis Common Mapper - Easy to use
column43: # MyBatis 通用 Mapper4þþ[![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/abel533/Mapper.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/abel533/Mapper)þ[![Maven central](https://maven-badges.herokuapp.com/maven-central/tk.mybatis/mapper/badge.svg)](https://maven-badges.herokuapp.com/maven-central/tk.mybatis/mapper)þþ通用Mapper都可以极大的方便开发人员。可以随意的按照自己的需要选择通用方法，还可以很方便的开发自己的通用方法。þþ极其方便的使用MyBatis单表的增删改查。þþ支持单表操作，不支持通用的多表联合查询。þþ**通用 Mapper 支持 Mybatis-3.2.4 及以上版本。**þþ## [**快速入门 - MyBatis 为什么需要通用 Mapper ?**](https://blog.csdn.net/isea533/article/details/83045335)þþ简介: 在早期项目文档中有过类似主题的内容，但是最近我自己看文档的时候发现一个问题，文档虽然很详细，但是并不适合初次接触的人。为了方便第一次听说，第一次尝试的开发人员了解通用 Mapper，补充此文档。þþ强烈建议初学者阅读本文，先从整体上了解 通用 Mapper，然后再通过下面的文档更深入的了解。þþ## 项目文档þþ- [文档 - Gitee](https://gitee.com/free/Mapper/wikis/Home)  þþ- [文档 - GitHub](https://github.com/abel533/Mapper/wiki)þþ- [JavaDoc](https://apidoc.gitee.com/free/Mapper/)þþ- [更新日志 - Gitee](https://gitee.com/free/Mapper/wikis/changelog)þþ- [更新日志 - GitHub](https://github.com/abel533/Mapper/wiki/changelog)þþ## 作者信息þ   þ   MyBatis 工具网站:[http://mybatis.tk](http://www.mybatis.tk)þ   þ   作者博客：http://blog.csdn.net/isea533þ   þ   作者邮箱： abel533@gmail.comþ   þ   如需加群，请通过 http://mybatis.tk 首页按钮加群。þ   þ   推荐使用Mybatis分页插件:[PageHelper分页插件](https://github.com/pagehelper/Mybatis-PageHelper)þ   þ## 作者新书：《MyBatis 从入门到精通》þþ![MyBatis 从入门到精通](https://github.com/mybatis-book/book/raw/master/book.png)þþ### 简介þþ本书中从一个简单的 MyBatis 查询入手，搭建起学习 MyBatis 的基础开发环境。þ通过全面的示例代码和测试讲解了在 MyBatis XML 方式和注解方式中进行增、删、改、查操作的基本用法，介绍了动态 SQL 在不同方面的应用以及在使用过程中的最佳实践方案。þ针对 MyBatis 高级映射、存储过程和类型处理器提供了丰富的示例，通过自下而上的方法使读者更好地理解和掌握MyBatis 的高级用法，同时针对 MyBatis 的代码生成器提供了详细的配置介绍。þ此外，本书还提供了缓存配置、插件开发、Spring、Spring Boot 集成的详细内容。þ最后通过介绍 Git 和 GitHub 让读者了解MyBatis 开源项目，通过对 MyBatis 源码和测试用例的讲解让读者更好掌握 MyBatis。þþ### 购买地址：þþ- [京东](https://item.jd.com/12103309.html)þþ- [当当](http://product.dangdang.com/25098208.html)þþ- [亚马逊](https://www.amazon.cn/MyBatis从入门到精通-刘增辉/dp/B072RC11DM/ref=sr_1_18?ie=UTF8&qid=1498007125&sr=8-18&keywords=mybatis)þþ### 相关介绍þþ- CSDN博客：http://blog.csdn.net/isea533/article/details/73555400þþ- GitHub项目：https://github.com/mybatis-book/book

column43: # KarutaþþThis repository contains the source code of the Karuta backend. This projectþprovides the logic layer of the Karuta project ; to fully set it up, you alsoþneed to install :þþ* [Karuta frontend](https://github.com/karutaproject/karuta-frontend)þ* [Karuta fileserver](https://github.com/karutaproject/karuta-fileserver)þþ## InstallationþþTo install this project, you need the following requirements:þþ* MySQL 5 or 8þ* Java 8+þ* TomcatþþThen, you need to do the following steps:þþ* Download the WAR archive and put it in the `webapps/` folder ofþ  your Tomcat installation.þ* Create a MySQL databaseþ* Then, configure the connection to the database by placing a fileþ  called `application.properties` inside the `lib/config` directoryþ  of Tomcat.þ  þ  You can use [this one](karuta-webapp/src/main/resources/application.properties)þ  as a basis.þþ## Additional documentationþþIf you are looking for the documentation of the different availableþendpoints, once the application is started, you can go to theþ`/rest/api/docs/index.html` URL.þþOn the other hand, here are some additional documentation for developers:þþ* [Introduction](docs/01-intro.md)þ* [Security](docs/02-security.md)þ* [Tests](docs/03-tests.md)þþ## LicenseþþKaruta is distributed under the terms of the ECL (Educational CommunityþLicense) version 2.0. You can check out the `LICENSE` file for furtherþinformation.

column43: Xabber - XMPP client for Androidþ================================þþOpen source Jabber (XMPP) client with multi-account support, clean and simple interface.þBeing both free (as in freedom!) and ad-free, Xabber is designed to be the best Jabber client for Android.þþBuild instrustionsþ==================þþXabber uses Gradle build system. The only specific thing is git submodule for otr4j library. To make it work use following commands:þþ ::þ þ git submodule initþ þ git submodule updateþ þAnd otr4j would be cloned to your local repository. þþSupported protocolsþ===================þþ* RFC-3920: Coreþ* RFC-3921: Instant Messaging and Presenceþ* XEP-0030: Service Discoveryþ* XEP-0128: Service Discovery Extensionsþ* XEP-0115: Entity Capabilitiesþ* XEP-0054: vcard-tempþ* XEP-0153: vCard-Based Avatarsþ* XEP-0045: Multi-User Chat (incompletely)þ* XEP-0078: Non-SASL Authenticationþ* XEP-0138: Stream Compressionþ* XEP-0203: Delayed Deliveryþ* XEP-0091: Legacy Delayed Deliveryþ* XEP-0199: XMPP Pingþ* XEP-0147: XMPP URI Scheme Query Componentsþ* XEP-0085: Chat State Notificationsþ* XEP-0184: Message Delivery Receiptsþ* XEP-0155: Stanza Session Negotiationþ* XEP-0059: Result Set Managementþ* XEP-0136: Message Archivingþ* XEP-0224: Attentionþ* XEP-0077: In-Band RegistrationþþTranslationsþ============þþþþWe use crowdin.com as our translation system.þAll related resources are automatically generated from files got with crowdin.com.þIf you want to update any translation go to Xabber page https://crowdin.com/project/xabber and request to join our translation teamþPlease don't create pull requests with translation fixes as any changes will be overwritten with the next update from crowdin.com.þþWikiþ====þþVisit our wiki pages for additional information: https://github.com/redsolution/xabber-android/wiki

Umple: Model-Oriented Programming - embed models in code and vice versa and generate complete systems
column43: # Umple Modelling Languageþþ### Build StatusþþOS         | Linux  | OSX    | Windows  þ:--------- | ------ | ------ | -------- þ**Status** | [![Travis-CI Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/umple/umple.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/umple/umple) | [![Travis-CI Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/umple/umple.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/umple/umple) | [![Windows Build status](https://ci.appveyor.com/api/projects/status/1yetvadynui7r8y6?svg=true)](https://ci.appveyor.com/project/vahdat-ab/umple/branch/master) þþþ## DescriptionþþThis is the main project for various Umple subprojects and components.þþUmple is a model-oriented programming technology, allowing developers to embed modelling concepts (e.g. UML associations, state machines), patterns, generation templates, and other abstractions in traditional code, and vice versa. It generates high quality code for Java, C++ and PhP, as well as diagrams, metrics and many other artifacts. It can be embeded in the above languages as well as embed them.þþThe project homepage is located at http://umple.org/þþThere are a large number of scientific papers about Umple listed at: http://publications.umple.orgþþ## Development ProcessþUmple is developed in itself, guaranteeing robustness; the most recent version of the compiler must be used to compile itself. See the wiki for development setup: http://devsetup.umple.orgþþDevelopment follows a model-driven, test-driven, agile, continuous-integration process. Umple is hosted currently on Github at http://code.umple.org. It was first released in 2007. The master was on Google Code from 2011 to mid 2015 and moved to Github in 2015.þþUmple has been largely developed as a research project at the University of Ottawa, Canada, by numerous PhD and masters students. Many undergraduates from across Canada and the USA have also contributed through the UCOSP program. See the license file for the list of contributors. http://license.umple.orgþþ## Installation and DownloadingþþUmple does not need necessarily to be downloaded, the following allow you to run it directly in any web browser:þþ  * UmpleOnline: http://try.umple.org - Website for the GUI version of Umple þ  * Docker: http://docker.umple.org - Install a docker image to run the GUI directlyþþYou can download the java jar for command-line use, or the Eclipse plugin:þþ  * Download page: http://dl.umple.org    - Links to the latest official release and continuous builds (command-line, Eclipse, Docker)þ  þTo run locally on your machine, Umple needs Java (versions 8-13) installed. It runs on Mac, Linux and Windows.þ  þ## UsageþþUmple is a programming and modeling language with a rich syntax. Full documentation with many examples can be found at þþ  * Umple user manual: http://manual.umple.org þþ## Other Key linksþþ  * Umple home page: http://www.umple.org  - The master Umple page with a more comprehensive set of linksþ  *  - Full documentation of all Umple featuresþ  * Live diagram of the metamodel: http://metamodel.umple.orgþ  * Architecture: http://architecture.umple.orgþþUmple is continuously tested and built at the University of Ottawa using CruiseControl; see http://cc.umple.org . It is also built on Travis CI (http://travis.umple.org/) and Appveyor (https://appveyor.com/).þþ## Contributingþþ  * Please report any bugs or improvement requests at: http://bugs.umple.orgþ  * To set up your development environment please see: http://devsetup.umple.orgþ  * For more details on contributing, please see: https://github.com/umple/umple/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.mdþþ## LicenseþþUmple is licensed under the MIT license. See http://license.umple.orgþþ## CreditsþþAll developers of Umple are listed in the license file at http://license.umple.orgþþFinancial support has been received from NSERC and the Ontario Research Fund. IBM supported early development of Umple. Google and Facebook supported student travel during Umple's development. þþ## Contents of the directoriesþþThe umple project is split into many smaller subprojects; the folder hierarchy is explained below to better describe the structure.þþ* build/þ  * Ant build scripts and related information including user manual raw dataþþ* cruise.umple/ *Umple compiler*þ  * See its own ReadMe.txt for further detailsþ  * See also UmpleTo* below for additional compiler componentsþ       þ* cruise.umple.eclipse/, cruise.umple.xtext.ui/ *Eclipse plugins*þþ* cruise.umplificator *Converting outside code to Umple*þ  * cruise.umple.validator *Validates umple when umplifying*þþ* cruise.umple.nebula *Infrastructure used for real-time C++*þþ* dev-tools *Tooling for Umple developers*þ       þ* dist *Build produced items, only available after building*þ  * libs/ *Managed build dependencies that umple*.jar require to run* þ  * cruise.umple/reference *User manual* þ  * qa/ *Test reports* þ  * umple.jar and umple.VERSION.jar  *Current command-line Compiler* þ  * umpledocs.VERSION.jar *User manual generator*þ  * umplestats.VERSION.jar *Statistics generation*þ  * umplesync.VERSION.jar *UmpleOnline tool to to synchronize graphical form*þ  * umplerun.VERSION.jar *tool to drive input to an umple program*þ  * vml.VERSION.jar * Extension for variability modeling*þ  * umple.unit-test.jar *Test Language Compiler*þ  * umple.mutation.jar *Umple Mutant Generator*þþ* examples/ *Developer curated examples*þ* externalexamples/ *External projects that are used for testing*þþ* ExternalTextEditorPlugins *Plugins for external editors, Notepad++, etc*þþ* sandbox *Small test done before a build to make sure testing and compiling works*þþ* testbed/, testbed_php/, testbed_ruby/ *Test suites for Java, Php and Ruby respectively*þ* UmpleToJava/ *Code generation for Java*þ* UmpleToPhp/ *Code generation for Php*þ* UmpleToRuby/ *Code generation for Ruby*þ* UmpleToRTCpp/ *Code generation for C++ *þ* UmpleToSDL/ *Code generation to convert Umple to SDL* (in early development)þ* UmpleToSql/ *Code generation SQL from Umple models*þ* UmpleToTest/ *Code generation for abstract tests*þ* UmpleToTemplate/ *Location for templates that could be common to subprojects*þ* UmpleTToJunit/ *Code Generation for JUnit5 - used by MTL compiler*þ* UmpleTToPhpunit/ *Code Generation for PhpUnit - used by MTL compiler*þ* UmpleTToRubyunit/ *Code Generation for RubyUnit - used by MTL compiler*þ* umpleonline/ *The UmpleOnline web application*þ  * UmpleOnline allows generation of code from Umple directly in a web browser, and also editing of Umple both graphically and textually. Available at http://try.umple.orgþþ þ* Umplificator/ *Reverse engineer code to Umple*þ* umplificatoronline/ *Online tool for converting code to Umple*þþ* umpleUI/ *Projects for the UIGU tooling*þ  * Projects for generating a UI through UIGU from Umple. These need work to incorporate them into UmpleOnlineþ        þ* umplewww/ *Core files from the Umple.org web pages*þ  * Includes items such as the user manual that are moved at build time into the appropriate place
